{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LzVHjBzkCyAU6uLwspUmn2","type":"tool_result","content":"**promptlibrary — WCAG accessibility attributes across all interactive components (PR #20, auto-merged)**\n- Refactored `StarRating` component: `role=\"radiogroup\"` with `aria-checked` radio buttons, arrow key keyboard navigation between stars, `focus-visible` ring styling\n- Added tab semantics to `PromptDetail` tabs: `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `aria-selected`, `aria-controls`, `id`-linked `tabpanel` elements\n- Added tab semantics to `MyPrompts` filter tabs: `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `aria-selected`\n- Converted visibility toggle in submit page to `role=\"switch\"` with `aria-checked` and `aria-label`\n- Connected all form labels to inputs via `htmlFor`/`id` across submit page (5 fields), output form (2 fields), rating form (1 field), settings page (1 field + sr-only label)\n- Replaced empty `alt=\"\"` on all avatar images with descriptive alt text (\"username's avatar\") in Nav, PromptCard, and PromptDetail (5 instances)\n- Added `role=\"alert\"` to all error message containers for screen reader live announcements (4 instances across submit, my-prompts, output form, rating form, settings)\n- Added contextual `aria-label` to revoke buttons in settings (\"Revoke API key {name}\")\n- 7 files changed, 66 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — app running (302 redirect to auth)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **promptlibrary**: Accessibility now solid for all interactive controls. Remaining opportunities: component-level React tests (would need jsdom), skip-to-content link, heading hierarchy audit\n- **scripts**: Has MutationObserver memory leak in Callisto Auto Control Setup, hardcoded LDAP names in Callisto PageKey, code duplication between userscript and extension — but these are personal automation scripts, low priority\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 42\n\n### What was done\n\n**promptlibrary — ESLint configuration with TypeScript and Next.js rules (PR #22, auto-merged)**\n- Added standalone ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with:\n  - TypeScript support via `typescript-eslint`\n  - React hooks plugin (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`)\n  - Next.js plugin (`@next/eslint-plugin-next`)\n  - Node.js globals for server-side files (lib/, api/, middleware)\n  - Extension directory excluded (browser JS with chrome/document globals)\n- Fixed 2 lint errors surfaced by the new config:\n  - `src/app/my-prompts/page.tsx`: `<a>` tag → `<Link>` from `next/link` (no-html-link-for-pages)\n  - `src/lib/sanitize.ts`: removed unnecessary regex escape `\\/` → `/` in bearer token pattern\n- Added `npm run lint` script to package.json\n- Added lint step to CI workflow (runs before type check)\n- Result: 0 errors, 5 warnings (all expected no-img-element for external OAuth avatar URLs)\n- 66 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — app running (302 redirect to auth)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **promptlibrary**: Now has linting. Remaining opportunities: component-level React tests (would need jsdom), skip-to-content link, heading hierarchy audit\n- **trustedCircle**: Still missing ESLint setup — good candidate for next session\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 43\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — ESLint configuration with TypeScript and React hooks rules (PR #43, auto-merged)**\n- Added standalone ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with:\n  - TypeScript support via `typescript-eslint`\n  - React hooks plugin (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`)\n  - Node.js globals for server-side files\n  - PM2 ecosystem config excluded\n- Fixed 9 lint errors surfaced by the new config:\n  - Removed 6 unused imports: `StarRating` (CategoryPage), `FeedResponse`/`Category` (CirclePage), `Users` (HomePage), `eq` (seed.ts), `beforeAll` (routes.test.ts)\n  - Replaced unsafe `Function` type with explicit `(...args: unknown[]) => void` in test helper\n  - Fixed `setState`-in-effect pattern in `useApi` hook (guarded with mounted ref)\n- Added `npm run lint` script to package.json\n- Added lint step to CI workflow (runs before type check)\n- Result: 0 errors, 0 warnings, 136 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Now has linting. All Tier 1-3 features complete, 136 tests, CI with lint/check/test/build/smoke.\n- **groceryGenius**: Missing standalone ESLint setup (currently uses `next lint` which may break on Next.js upgrades like runeval did)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 44\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Comprehensive WCAG accessibility pass (PRs #44-#45, auto-merged)**\n- **Card component**: Added keyboard support (Enter/Space to activate) with focus ring for all clickable cards across the app\n- **ReactionButtons**: Added `aria-pressed` toggle state and `aria-label` with counts on both helpful/agree buttons\n- **SortPills**: Added `aria-pressed` on active pill, `role=\"group\"` with label on container\n- **StarRating**: Added `role=\"img\"` with descriptive `aria-label` (\"Rating: X.X out of 5 stars\")\n- **TrustBadges**: Added `aria-label` on badges, `aria-hidden` on decorative icons\n- **Header**: `aria-label` on nav, search form `role=\"search\"`, `sr-only` label for search input, `aria-current=\"page\"` on active nav link, `aria-label` on all nav links (for mobile icon-only view)\n- **App.tsx**: Wrapped page content in `<main>` landmark\n- **ReviewerSelector (ComparePage)**: Added `aria-haspopup=\"listbox\"`, `aria-expanded`, `role=\"listbox\"`/`role=\"option\"`, Escape key to close\n- **All back buttons** (4 pages): Added `aria-label`\n- **All search inputs** (3 locations): Associated `<label>` elements via `htmlFor`/`id`\n- **All filter pill groups** (3 pages): `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label`, `aria-pressed` on each pill\n- **40+ decorative Lucide icons**: Marked `aria-hidden=\"true\"` across 14 files\n- **Non-semantic interactive elements**: Replaced clickable `<span>`s with `<button>`s in ReviewCard and CirclePage FeedCard; wrapped clickable `<h2>` content in `<button>` on ComparePage\n- **Pagination (CategoryPage)**: Wrapped in `<nav aria-label=\"Pagination\">`, added `aria-label` on prev/next buttons\n- **Follow button (PersonPage)**: Added `aria-pressed` toggle state\n- **Load more button (CirclePage)**: Added `aria-busy` during loading\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 136 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Now fully accessible. All Tier 1-3 features complete, 136 tests, CI with lint/check/test/build/smoke.\n- **groceryGenius**: Already has standalone ESLint (Vite project, not Next.js — previous note was incorrect). Already had WCAG pass (Run 40).\n- **promptlibrary**: Already had WCAG pass (Run 41) and ESLint (Run 42).\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: runeval (main product, no a11y pass yet), valueSortify, pezantTools\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ce4fce5-7113-4c5a-aac1-c11f62c26018","uuid":"a9a857b4-15e8-4e92-857d-dc3f86fa015b","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:50:51.249Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"**promptlibrary — WCAG accessibility attributes across all interactive components (PR #20, auto-merged)**\n- Refactored `StarRating` component: `role=\"radiogroup\"` with `aria-checked` radio buttons, arrow key keyboard navigation between stars, `focus-visible` ring styling\n- Added tab semantics to `PromptDetail` tabs: `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `aria-selec